The White House has announced that Susan E. "Susie" Morrison will be the next White House Executive Pastry Chef. She is the seventh person and the first woman to serve in this role. Morrison will be responsible for the day-to-day operations of the pastry kitchen and will create and execute dessert menus for social events at the White House. She has been working at the Executive Residence since 1995 and has worked with previous Executive Pastry Chefs. Morrison is also interested in supporting the health of the bee population and tends to the White House bee hive. In her free time, she enjoys cycling, running, swimming, and surfing.